Genuinely the worst Starbucks in NYC in terms of service.  It's always empty and yet they are chronically out of coffee and fill orders at a glacial pace.  One of their many tricks to avoid work: if customer orders, say, Pike. and they are out, they will slyly give you blonde or dark and hope you didn't notice.  They will keep at it until called out and then grudgingly make more coffee.  More than half the employees here have never made eye contact with a customer.  Notable pluses: two free bathrooms that are amazingly clean.  Nice outdoor space on the sidewalk.  Plenty of seating most days indoors.
